Package net.marfgamer.jraknet

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Packet
    Used to read and write data with ease.
    RakNet
    Contains info for RakNet
    RakNetClientTest
    Used to test RakNetClient by connecting to the LifeBoat Survival Games server, sending a dummy packet to make sure the ACK/NACK functions work, and then disconnecting afterwards.
    RakNetPacket
    A generic RakNet packet that has the ability to get the ID of the packet along with encoding and decoding.
    RakNetServerTest
    Used to test RakNetServer by starting a server on the default Minecraft port.
    SequencedPacketTest
    Used to test the sequenced packet feature of RakNetSession through a stress test by sending 1000 packets and seeing if any were lost (Completely lost or received before the earlier one could be handled, as the reliability used in this test is UNRELIABLE_SEQUENCED).
    SplitPacketTest
    Used to test the split packet feature of RakNetSession through a stress test by sending a packet as big as possible (Average packet size is over 146,000 bytes!).
    UtilityTest
    Used to test the various functions in RakNetUtils.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    NoListenerException
    Signals that there is no set listener for the server/client.
    RakNetException
    Signals an exception related to RakNet.
